Document: EditorInspectorPlugin
Path: godot/classes/class_editorinspectorplugin.rst
Summary: Describes how to create custom property editors for the Godot Inspector using the EditorInspectorPlugin class.
EditorInspectorPlugin allows adding custom property editors to EditorInspector. When an object is edited, the _can_handle function is called and must return true if the object type is supported. If supported, the function _parse_begin will be called, allowing to place custom controls at the beginning of the class. Subsequently, the _parse_category and _parse_property are called for every category and property. They offer the ability to add custom controls to the inspector too. Finally, _parse_end will be called. On each of these calls, the "add" functions can be called. To use EditorInspectorPlugin, register it using the EditorPlugin.add_inspector_plugin method first.
---CHUNK---
Document: EditorInspectorPlugin
Path: godot/classes/class_editorinspectorplugin.rst
Summary: This document provides an overview of the EditorInspectorPlugin class in Godot Engine, which is used for creating custom inspectors.

Inherits: EditorInspectorExtension < RefCounted

This class is the base for creating custom inspector plugins. These plugins allow you to extend the default inspector behavior for specific node types or resources.

Methods:

Method: _can_handle(object: Object) → bool
Returns true if the plugin can handle the given object. This is called by the inspector to determine if this plugin should be used.

Method: _parse_begin(object: Object)
Called when the inspector starts parsing an object.

Method: _parse_end(object: Object)
Called when the inspector finishes parsing an object.

Method: _update_property_list(object: Object)
This method is called when the property list for an object is about to be generated. You can use it to add, remove, or modify properties in the list.

Key Rule: The `_update_property_list` method is the primary way to customize the inspector's displayed properties.

Method: _get_property_value(object: Object, name: NodePath) → Variant
Returns the value of a property. This is called when the inspector needs to display a property's value.

Method: _set_property_value(object: Object, name: NodePath, value: Variant)
Sets the value of a property. This is called when the user modifies a property in the inspector.

Method: _get_property_name_tooltip(object: Object, name: NodePath) → String
Returns the tooltip for a property.

Method: _get_property_icon(object: Object, name: NodePath) → Texture2D
Returns the icon for a property.

Method: _get_property_editor(object: Object, name: NodePath) → Control
Returns a custom editor control for a property. If null, the default editor is used.

Method: _property_changed(object: Object, name: NodePath, value: Variant)
Called when a property has been changed by the user or programmatically.

Method: _get_configuration_warnings(object: Object) → PackedStringArray
Returns a list of configuration warnings for the object.

Method: _get_help_text(object: Object, name: NodePath) → String
Returns the help text for a property.

Method: _get_custom_name_for_property(object: Object, name: NodePath) → String
Returns a custom name for a property.

